race.comment: Another tough Highway. FINGERS HUNTER (2) drops in trip and set to peak at her third run back. Saved ground along the inside with the 59.5kg to secure fourth over 1400m at Rosehill in the soft going. Will appreciate Nock's claim and a host of gear changes. Go close. MARTINI MUMMA (7) proven at this level and gets her chance from the inside gate. Covered a stack of ground first-up with a tenacious on-pace third over this track and trip. Proven second-up and sure to be thereabouts. AUTUMN BREAK (12) sharp on-pace gelding resuming. Undefeated in three starts in weaker company and deserves his chance in town. Returns with the one slick trial win over 900m and the booking of Tim Clark is a positive. ATMOSPHERIC ROCK (3) caught the eye at the big odds last start and can surprise again.
